<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-720-384  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 720 384.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  July 26 1990 n1224 p78(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Keep an eye out for any unethical employee about. (computer crime)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Whyte, Gemma.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Employees should be encouraged to inform management aboutunethical actions by fellow workers, especially in the informationtechnology (IT) industry where computer crimes can have disastrousconsequences.andP;  The IT industry is becoming famous for its problemswith computer hackers and viruses.andP;  Whistle blowing can act as asafety net when serious crime has slipped through a company'sdefenses.andP;  Companies should employ these five steps: publish theircorporate philosophy; define the business mission, including acode of ethics; provide a code that clearly defines the rights andresponsibilities of employees and management; help all employeesunderstand the ethical element in their daily choices; and developways to monitor ethical performance inside and outside theorganization.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer CrimesComputer VirusesData SecurityEmployee RelationsManagement Style.andO;Feature:   illustrationcartoon.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>